  "name": "Heartstone",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>This gemstone grants its wearer a +2 item bonus to saving throws.</p>\n<p>Each <em>heartstone</em> is powered by the spirit of a specific night hag. If it's separated from her for 24 hours (or she's been dead for 24 hours), it becomes a nonmagical gemstone. A heartstone allows the hag to use additional occult innate spells: <em>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.D2nPKbIS67m9199U]{Ethereal Jaunt}</em> (9th level) and <em>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.GYmXvS9NJ7QwfWGg]{Bind Soul}</em> at will, and <em>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.IqJ9URobmJ9L9UBG]{Shadow Blast}</em> twice per day.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">1</span> command</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong> You must be touching the <em>heartstone</em>.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> The <em>heartstone</em> attempts to counteract one disease affecting you (counteract level 5, counteract modifier [[/r {1d20+18} #Counteract Modifier]]{+18}).</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Craft Requirements</strong> You must be a night hag.</p>"
